input.issue_body:
This behavior worked in 2.0.26-beta but causes an error in 2.0.33-beta.  

See https://github.com/emosesSfdc/mockito-default-mock-repro for a repro case.  Its tests pass in .26, but one of them fails in .33 with the error:

```
Cannot call abstract real method on java object!
Calling real methods is only possible when mocking non abstract method.
  //correct example:
  when(mockOfConcreteClass.nonAbstractMethod()).thenCallRealMethod();
org.mockito.exceptions.base.MockitoException: 
Cannot call abstract real method on java object!
Calling real methods is only possible when mocking non abstract method.
  //correct example:
  when(mockOfConcreteClass.nonAbstractMethod()).thenCallRealMethod();
    at mockitoTest.ApplicationTest.testGetValue(ApplicationTest.java:16)
    at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)
...
```

If you have an interface 

```
public interface I {
    default String m() { return "m"; }
}
```

And a concrete implementation that doesn't override `m()`, 

```
public class Impl implements I {}
```

Then if you try 

```
I i = Mockito.spy(new Impl());
Mocktio.when(i.m()).thenReturn("other");
i.m();
```

You'll get the above error.

